In this statement, the President of the United States commemorates the International Day in Support of Victims of Torture. He emphasizes that torture is inconsistent with American values and affirms that the United States is committed to eradicating this practice. The President highlights that torture and abusive treatment not only violate our values but also undermine national security by serving as a recruitment tool for terrorists. He states that torture is ineffective in obtaining accurate information. The United States remains dedicated to supporting the United Nations Voluntary Fund for Victims of Torture and providing funding for programs that assist and counsel torture victims. Additionally, the country supports efforts to end torture globally through human rights training, improving prison conditions, and developing strong laws against torture.